  "body": "I actually surprised, why did you set unix timestamp for the Shanghai fork at #26908?\r\nFor all previous forks the point of fork was always set to the block number instead of timestamp, and this was pretty clear, because the `timestamp` synchronization is a tricky in a distributed system, but the block number is a straight way for the Ethereum protocol as the reference point.\r\nThere are [no engough checks for the `block timestamp` on the consensus layer as well](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/consensus/ethash/consensus.go#L279), so, the question seems reasonable.",
